### 3. Efficiency: Weighted DSU on Tree
You used `order[u] = cols[u].size()`. This is actually an **optimized** version of DSU on tree. Standard DSU on tree uses subtree size ($sz[u]$), but since your processing time is proportional to the number of elements in `cols[u]`, using the sum of `cols.size()` as the "weight" to determine the heavy child is more efficient. This is a good practice.

