```
In "DSU on Tree," when you move from one component to another, if you don't reset `colcnt[x]`, the counts from the previous component will "leak" into the next one. If Answer `1` appeared 5 times in Component A, the first time it appears in Component B, `colcnt[1]` will become `6`.

### 3. The `clear()` Efficiency
Resetting `colcnt` for all $10^5$ possible answers using `memset` or a full loop inside `clear()` would be $O(N)$ per call, making the total complexity $O(N^2)$. You must only reset the values you actually changed.

